But Being a mummy is the toughest job in the world - but it's the best thing ever. To all the mummy's out here having a rough day, feeling exhausted , like they can't cope , wondering if they are the only ones feeling it let me tell you - YOURE NOT ALONE. Very normal to feel all of the above many times / kids teach us so much and constantly challenge us as parents and humans , our patience , understanding , compassion , learning skills and so much more. Take one day at a time , reach out for support when you need it and just know that every tantrum , challenge , long day will past. In saying that there is some long days but the years fly by and before you know it they have grown up! So try to enjoy as much of it as you can ( tantrums are fun said no mum ever ) BUT you know what I mean.
Also make sure you do a check in on social media and who your following , make sure it's people who empower you, inspire you and motivate you to step up in the world and be the happiest healthiest BEST version of yourself! Anyone else you aren't giving click unfollow ✌🏼 GO on do it!

Each of us has had a different start to life, and that’s shaped us into who we are today. .
Every conversation, everything we’ve seen and every lesson a long the way has provided the framework for who we are as a person. .
What we choose to do with that of course is completely up to us. .
You can choose to let your past and your lessons be the reason you want to succeed today, or the reason that you give up. .
The amount of energy required is the same but both will give you totally different results - different life. .
It’s today and tomorrow that really count so how can you live yours to the full? How have you been living up untill now and is it time to change. .
#deep questions for 4 am in the morning I know but hay if this can help one person it's worth it. 💕
